{"title_page": "2011 Super League Grand Final", "text_new": "{{Infobox rugby league football match\n|year         = 2011\n|title        = Super League Grand Final\n|image        = \n|imagesize    = 300px\n|alt          = 2011 Super League logo\n|home         = [[St Helens R.F.C.|St. Helens]] \n|away         = [[Leeds Rhinos]] \n|home_abbr    = ST H {{leagueicon|St Helens|16}}\n|away_abbr    = LEE {{leagueicon|Leeds Rhinos|16}}\n|home_half1   = 2\n|home_half2   = 14\n|home_total   = 16\n|away_half1   = 8\n|away_half2   = 24\n|away_total   = 32\n|date         = 8 October 2011\n|stadium      = [[Old Trafford (football ground)|Old Trafford]]\n|location     = {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Manchester]]\n|MoM_title    = [[Harry Sunderland Trophy]]\n|MoM          = {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Rob Burrow]] ({{leagueicon|Leeds|16}} [[Leeds Rhinos]])\n|anthem_title = Headliners\n|anthem       = [[Feeder (band)|Feeder]]\n|referee      = [[Phil Bentham]]\n|attendance   = 69,107\n|network      = [[Sky Sports]]\n|commentators = [[Eddie Hemmings (rugby league)|Eddie Hemmings]]\n|commentators2= [[Mike Stephenson]]\n|commentators3= [[Phil Clarke]]\n|commentators4= [[Shaun McRae]]\n|tournaments  = [[Super League Grand Final]]\n|last         = [[2010 Super League Grand Final|2010]]\n|next         = [[2012 Super League Grand Final|2012]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2011 Super League Grand Final''' was the conclusive and championship-deciding game of the [[Super League XVI]] season. It was held on Saturday, 8 October at [[Manchester, England]]'s [[Old Trafford (football ground)|Old Trafford]] stadium. The match was contested by [[St Helens R.F.C.|St. Helens]] and the [[Leeds Rhinos]], who last faced each other in a grand final in 2009. British rock band [[Feeder (band)|Feeder]] were due to provide the pre-match music entertainment, only for their show to be called off due to the pitch being wet and [[Manchester United]] manager [[Alex Ferguson]] not allowing a stage to be built on the pitch. Leeds won the game by 32 points to 16.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2011/oct/08/super-league-grand-final-match-report?newsfeed=true|title=Leeds claim Grand Final glory as inspired Rob Burrow sinks St Helens|date=8 October 2011|work=Guardian|accessdate=11 October 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/rugbyleague/8815944/St-Helens-16-Leeds-32-match-report.html|title=St Helens 16 Leeds 32|date=8 October 2011|work=Daily Telegraph|accessdate=11 October 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Position\"| #\n! style=\"width:175px;\"| Team\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Played\"| Pld\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Won\"| W\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Drawn\"| D\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Lost\"| L\n! style=\"width:25px;\" abbr=\"Points for\"| PF\n! style=\"width:25px;\" abbr=\"Points against\"| PA\n! style=\"width:25px;\" abbr=\"Points difference\"| PD\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Points\"| Pts\n|- \n| 3 ||style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Image:Saintscolours.svg|16x16px]] [[St Helens R.F.C.|St. Helens]]\n| 27 || 17 || 3 || 7 || 782 || 515 || +267 || '''37'''\n|- \n| 5 ||style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Image:Rhinoscolours.svg|16x16px]] [[Leeds Rhinos]]\n| 27 || 15 || 1 || 11 || 757 || 603 || +154 || '''31'''\n|}\n\n===Route to the Final===\n====St Helens====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;margin-left:1em;float:right\"\n<!-- |+ '''Leeds''' -->\n!width=\"25\" | Round\n!width=\"150\" | Opposition\n!width=\"60\" | Score\n|-\n!scope=row style=\"text-align:center\"| Qualifying Play-Off \n| {{leagueicon|wigan|16}} [[Wigan Warriors]] (A)\n|bgcolor=DDFFDD| 26-18\n|-\n!scope=row style=\"text-align:center\"| Semi-Final\n| {{leagueicon|wigan|16}} [[Wigan Warriors]] (H)\n|bgcolor=DDFFDD| 26-18\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background-color:white;\"| <small>'''Key:''' (H) = Home venue; (A) = Away venue; (N) = [[Home advantage#Neutral venues|Neutra